    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MassQL parser. The parser transforms a query into an internal data structure that can be used by any programming language. The parsing is done by using the lark Python library (https://github.com/lark-parser/lark) and specific Python code to transform a MassQL query to a parse tree and into the internal data structure that organizes all query conditions and qualifiers.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the parser converting MassQL queries into structured representations (parse trees and internal data structures). Design principles of expressiveness, precision, scalability, and natural language readability are central to MassQL's design as stated in the abstract and introduction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-025-02660-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the Mass Spec Query Language parser convert MassQL query strings into structured representations while satisfying the design principles of expressiveness, precision, scalability, and natural language readability?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we introduce the Mass Spectrometry Query Language (MassQL), an open-source language for flexible and mass spectrometer manufacturer-independent searching.",
      "asbval:note": "MassQL is the primary subject of the paper and is extensively documented as the tool being developed and implemented.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-025-02660-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MassQL",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The parser transforms a query into an internal data structure that can be used by any programming language. The parsing is done by using the lark Python library (https://github.com/lark-parser/lark) and specific Python code to transform a MassQL query to a parse tree and into the internal data structure that organizes all query conditions and qualifiers.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes transformation into parse trees and internal data structures. JSON export is mentioned: 'Output results are data frames that can be exported as a tabular format. Optionally, the retrieved MS spectra can be exported in JSON format, MGF and mzML.'",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-025-02660-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Structured Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) or JSON representation of the parsed MassQL query",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MassQL language implements a succinct and expressive grammar to search for chemically and biologically relevant molecules in the MS data by leveraging these patterns... MassQL provides language support for user-defined tolerances, such as ion intensity and mass accuracy... Moreover, each of these query elements can be combined with Boolean operators (for example, AND, OR and NOT) to form more complex queries.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates expressiveness, precision (via tolerances), and natural language readability (via multi-language translation and documentation), but does not explicitly describe a formal 'parser validation report' as a deliverable. The design principles are validated through application examples and community adoption rather than a formal validation report artifact.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-025-02660-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Parser validation report confirming adherence to Expressiveness, Precision, Scalability, and Natural Language design principles",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we introduce a new language, the Mass Spectrometry Query Language (MassQL)... The MassQL formal grammar builds upon common MS terminology (Methods), which makes MassQL queries easy to write and alter for scientists with basic familiarity with MS.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes MassQL as inspired by SQL-like query paradigms and encodes MS-centric assumptions, but does not explicitly state 'SQL inspiration' in the passages provided. The grammar is described as building on 'common MS terminology' rather than explicitly referencing SQL as the design inspiration, though the query language structure is SQL-like.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-025-02660-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Implement MassQL query parser that encodes mass-spectrometry-centric assumptions from SQL inspiration",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card frames the task as implementing a parser, but the paper describes MassQL as an already-implemented, published language with multiple software implementations (MZmine, pyOpenMS, MS-DIAL, UniDec, Metabolomics Workbench, Bruker MetaboScape). The parser is a component of the reference implementation, not a future implementation task.",
        "The expected output 'Parser validation report' is not explicitly described as a paper deliverable; instead, the paper demonstrates validation through real-world application examples (siderophore discovery, OPE discovery) and community adoption metrics.",
        "The card's framing as a task to 'implement' the parser may conflate the paper's description of an already-implemented reference parser with a prospective implementation task."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:36:13.478095+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
